You could refactor a lot of code if you grouped all of the phase fields into a nested class.
public MeterModelBlock{
...
    public PhaseBlock phaseA = new PhaseBlock();
    public PhaseBlock phaseB = new PhaseBlock();
    public PhaseBlock phaseC = new PhaseBlock();
...

    public static class PhaseBlock {
...
        public Optional<Long> acExportedReactiveEnergyQ4;
...
    }
}

Then you could access all the data like so: meterBlock.phaseC.acExportedReactiveEnergyQ4.
Model parsing wouldn't be all that different, but where you would save a lot of code is in this class and in the handler where you would only need a single method to update all the channels for a phase group, rather than having a method for each phase like you do now.
WDYT?
